{{italic title}} '''''Domino Chance''''' is a [[comic]] originally [[published]] from 1982 through 1986 by [[Chance Enterprises]].<ref>Lenagh, Kevin (May 1982-Jan 1984) "Domino Chance"</ref> It would be later released under the title '''''Amazing Comics'''''.<ref>Lenagh, Kevin (1987) "Domino Chance" 1.1</ref> Written and drawn by [[Kevin Lenagh]], the series lasted ten issues. It was self-published by Kevin's wife Sandra Lenagh and was later re-issued.
It was a [[sci-fi]] story about ''The Scarab'', a spaceship captained by a cockroach named Domino Chance. He and the crew would do various odd-jobs for money.
This comic introduced [[Gizmo (comic book)|Gizmo Sprocket]], who made several appearances. Chance Enterprises also published Gizmo's first full-length comic before it moved to [[Mirage Studios]].
