'''John Monteith''' (November 1, 1948 - January 16, 2018) was an improvisor, writer, actor and director; mainly known for his work with the [[Monteith and Rand]] comedy team who had their own Broadway show at the [[Booth Theater]]<ref name="Internet Broadway Database">{{cite web|title=Rand and Monteith|url=http://ibdb.com/production.php?id=3912}}</ref> in 1979, produced by [[James Lipton]],<ref name=Bonanza>{{cite web|title=Rand and Monteith Playbill|url=http://www.bonanza.com/listings/Monteith-and-Rand-Playbill-Booth-Theater-1979-Producer-James-Lipton-Suzanne-Rand/80278499}}</ref> after a successful off-Broadway run. Their shows performed for the BBC were repackaged and sold to ABC as [[Whose Line Is It Anyway? (U.S. TV series)|Whose Line Is It Anyway?]]. John graduated from [[The Second City]];  Monteith lived in New York City where he taught and performed.<ref name="Working Actor Studio">{{cite web|title=John Monteith Bio|url=http://www.eyeblink.org/workingactorstudio/classInstructors/}}</ref> Monteith died on January 16, 2018.<ref name="Obituary">"{{cite web|title=Obituary|url=http://www.tributes.com/obituary/show/John-Monteith-105730494}}</ref><ref>[http://www.schneiderfuneralhome.net/obituary/John-Monteith/New-Jersey/1776122 John Monteith Obituary]</ref>

