{{Infobox company | name = Suzy Soft | logo = SuzySoftLogo.jpg | caption = | type = Software publishing subsidiary of [[Suzy Records]] | traded_as = | industry = {{unbulleted list|[[Video game industry|Video games]]|[[Software]]}} | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | foundation = 1985 | founder = | defunct = 1988 | location_city = [[Zagreb]], [[SR Croatia]] | location_country = [[Yugoslavia]] | area_served = [[Yugoslavia]] | key_people = | products = | production = | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | aum = <!-- Only used with financial services companies --> | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = [[Suzy Records]] | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = {{url|www.suzy.hr}} | footnotes = | intl = | bodystyle = }} '''Suzy Soft''' was a Yugoslav/Croatian [[video game publisher]] active during the 1980s. It started in 1985 as the software division of [[Suzy Records]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sk.rs/2014/10/skgk04.html |title=Svet Kompjutera - Gost Kolumnista - Aleksandar Radovanović |publisher=Sk.rs |date= |accessdate=2015-10-28}}</ref> based in [[Zagreb]],<ref>{{cite web|author=Kristian Benić |url=http://www.planb.hr/yu-gamer/ |title=YU Gamer « plan b – digitalna pop kultura |publisher=Planb.hr |date= |accessdate=2015-10-28}}</ref> and published video games and programs for [[ZX Spectrum]], [[Commodore 64]] and [[Orao (computer)|Orao]] by various Yugoslav developers. It was the first Yugoslav company dedicated to software publishing.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.planb.hr/geek-lokacije-koje-morate-posjetiti/ |title=Top 25: Hrvatske geek lokacije koje morate posjetiti « plan b – digitalna pop kultura |publisher=Planb.hr |date= |accessdate=2015-10-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://emulator.galaksija.org/MagScans/SK8802/SK8802-23.png |format=PNG |title=Suzy-Soft vam predstavlja |publisher=Emulator.galaksija.org |accessdate=2015-10-28}}</ref> The house became defunct in 1988, as its parent ditched the software publishing department.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamesthatwerent.com/gtw64/kljuc/ |title=Kljuc – 1988 Suzy Soft - Games That Weren't - GTW64 - home of unreleased Commodore 64 games |publisher=Gamesthatwerent.com |date=2012-10-04 |accessdate=2015-10-28}}</ref>
