{{Infobox album | name = Themes from Mr. Lucky, The Untouchables, and Other TV Action Jazz | type = studio | artist = [[Mundell Lowe]] | cover = TV Action Jazz Vol 2.jpg | released = {{Start date|1960}} | recorded = June 1 & 6, 1960 | studio = New York City | genre = [[Jazz]] | length = | label = [[RCA Camden]] | producer = Chick Crumpacker | chronology = [[Mundell Lowe]] | prev_title = [[TV Action Jazz!]] | prev_year = 1959 | next_title = [[Satan in High Heels#Soundtrack|Satan in High Heels]] | next_year = 1961 }}
'''''Themes from ''Mr. Lucky'', ''The Untouchables'' and Other TV Action Jazz''''' is the second album by American jazz guitarist [[Mundell Lowe]] with [[theme music]] from detective, legal, and police television programs. The album was recorded in 1960 for [[RCA Camden]].<ref name="jd">{{cite web |title=Mundell Lowe Catalog - album index |url=https://www.jazzdisco.org/mundell-lowe/catalog/album-index/ |website=www.jazzdisco.org |accessdate=31 October 2018}}</ref>
This album came after ''[[TV Action Jazz!]]'', Lowe's previous album of television theme songs. The record label Lone Hill Jazz combined both albums into one compilation, ''Complete TV Action Jazz''. ''Themes'' includes music from ''[[Markham (TV series)|Markham]]'', ''[[Mr. Lucky (TV series)|Mr. Lucky]]'', ''[[Johnny Staccato]]'', ''[[Tightrope!]]'', and ''[[The Untouchables (1959 TV series)|The Untouchables]]{{dn|date=December 2018}}''.<ref name="Myers">{{cite web |last1=Myers |first1=Marc |title=Mundell Lowe: TV Action Jazz - JazzWax |url=https://www.jazzwax.com/2010/08/mundell-lowe-tv-action-jazz.html |website=www.jazzwax.com |accessdate=31 October 2018}}</ref>
== Track listing == # "Theme from Tightrope" ([[George Duning]])&nbsp;– 2:52 # "Hawaiian Eye" ([[Jerry Livingston]], [[Mack David]])&nbsp;– 3:53 # "Theme from Mr. Lucky" ([[Henry Mancini]])&nbsp;– 3:11 # "Theme from the Untouchables" ([[Nelson Riddle]])&nbsp;– 2:53 # "Bourbon Street Beat" (Livingston, David)&nbsp;– 2:47 # "Detectives Theme" ([[Herschel Burke Gilbert]])&nbsp;– 2:32 # "Markham Theme" (Stanley Wilson)&nbsp;– 2:53 # "Johnny Staccato's Theme" ([[Elmer Bernstein]])&nbsp;– 4:00
